# This contains descriptions of folders in verb/inst.

configs - this contsins config files and data for apps and many server-wide settings often referred to by serfs
config - this contains verious initial config files, such as the etc folder, (ie Apache and Monit) that need to be copied only once upon install
make-apache - this is used as a base for creating the many Apache config files for the server
make-verb - this is used by make-name and make-name-preserver to create the pre-install server before running setupverb
make-email - this is used to set the email server to a domain other than .email
make-verb-domain - this is used to retrain the entire Verberâ„¢ server engine to use a custom domain, not verb.ink, verb.blue, etc.

